soc.server.database

Class DBSettingMismatchException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • soc.server.database.DBSettingMismatchException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DBSettingMismatchException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    This exception indicates SOCDBHelper.initialize(String, String, Properties) was called with one or more properties which are also in the settings table but with different values.

    Since SOCDBHelper prints a message when settings mismatch or are corrected, this Exception doesn't contain all info. Its Throwable.getMessage() is the first mismatched setting name which was found.

    Since:
    1.2.00
    Author:
    Jeremy D Monin <jeremy@nand.net>
    See Also:
    SOCDBHelper.PROP_JSETTLERS_DB_SETTINGS, Serialized Form

        public DBSettingMismatchException(java.lang.String settingKey)
        Create a DBSettingMismatchException; settingKey is the name of a mismatched setting. It will be placed into Throwable.getMessage().
        Parameters:
        settingKey - Key name of a mismatched setting, such as SOCDBHelper.SETTING_BCRYPT_WORK__FACTOR. If multiple settings are mismatched, provide only one of them.
